In practical terms: familiar music can literally slow your heart rate, lower stress hormones, and calm your breathing — your whole body shifts into a relaxed state.

Emotions Are Permanently Attached to Sounds Through Memory


Music-Evoked Autobiographical Memories (MEAM)



Why This Is Even Stronger in People with Dementia
For someone with dementia, most new information is confusing and frightening because the brain can no longer process it well. But familiar sounds bypass all that damaged processing. They go straight to the deep emotional memory centers that are still intact — which is why a person who can no longer recognize their own children can still smile and calm down when they hear a song from their youth.

